    <fr:title text="Cantor’s theorem">Cantor’s theorem</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Given any set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, there can be no <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7345</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6084</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6084.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Assume that we <fr:em>do</fr:em> have a <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Consider the subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U\in \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> defined below:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  U = {\mathopen {}\left \{x\in  A\,\middle \vert \,x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}\right \}\mathclose {}}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>, we may find some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=U]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Thus for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we have
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
   x\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}
   \Longleftrightarrow 
   x\in  U
   \Longleftrightarrow 
   x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}
 ]]></fr:tex>. Setting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:= a]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} \Longleftrightarrow  a\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, a contradiction.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
