                <fr:route>jms-00NJ.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Uncountability of the reals"><fr:link href="jms-00MH.xml" title="Countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">Uncountability</fr:link> of the reals</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> of real numbers is <fr:link href="jms-00MH.xml" title="Countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">uncountable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7639</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6086</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6086.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Of course, as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is non-empty, it is enough to show that it is not <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link>. We know that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left  [0,1\right  ]\mathclose {}}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\to {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}\cong  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and and it follows from <fr:link href="jms-00NF.xml" title="Cantor’s theorem" addr="jms-00NF" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00NF" /></fr:link> that the latter is not <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
