            <fr:title text="Uncountability of the reals › "><fr:link href="jms-00NJ.xml" title="Uncountability of the reals" addr="jms-00NJ" type="local"><fr:link href="jms-00MH.xml" title="Countable set" addr="jms-00MH" type="local">Uncountability</fr:link> of the reals</fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Of course, as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is non-empty, it is enough to show that it is not <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link>. We know that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left  [0,1\right  ]\mathclose {}}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\to {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}\cong  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and and it follows from <fr:link href="jms-00NF.xml" title="Cantor’s theorem" addr="jms-00NF" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00NF" /></fr:link> that the latter is not <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
